{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"SPIKE RESULT: PASS (definitive). Ran headless Claude Code v2.1.211 in an isolated temp dir with CLAUDE.md = '@AGENTS.md' and AGENTS.md holding a canary token; the model returned the canary VERBATIM with NO approval prompt -> a project-level @AGENTS.md import in CLAUDE.md expands AGENTS.md into Claude Code's context at launch. Official docs (code.claude.com/docs/en/memory) confirm and recommend exactly this pattern (@AGENTS.md + a ## Claude Code section). No symlink fallback needed. Downstream stories S2 (6642) and 5b01 build on this proven mechanism (thin CLAUDE.md = single @AGENTS.md import). Version tested: claude 2.1.211. No stray spike files left in the tree (throwaway temp dir)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784255638229601001,"uuid":"ec9be336-c51d-4ae1-8702-ccc7c1fd853b"}